# Backend Log Inspection

For backend logs, the project root is `C:\Users\gilak\Music\translate_chat`.

Use this PowerShell pattern to inspect the Render backend logs for this project. Adjust `$minutes` to control how far back to look.

```powershell
$minutes=5
$headers=@{
  Authorization="Bearer $($env:RENDER_API_KEY)"
  Accept="application/json"
}
$since=(Get-Date).ToUniversalTime().AddMinutes(-$minutes).ToString("yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ")
$service=Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "https://api.render.com/v1/services/srv-d760nv9r0fns73bqfung" -Headers $headers
$ownerId=$service.ownerId
$endTime=""
do {
  $url="https://api.render.com/v1/logs?ownerId=$ownerId&resource=srv-d760nv9r0fns73bqfung&startTime=$since&limit=500"
  if ($endTime) { $url+="&endTime=$endTime" }
  $res=Invoke-RestMethod -Uri $url -Headers $headers
  $res.logs | Where-Object { $_.message -notmatch 'GET /health' } | ForEach-Object { $_.message }
  $endTime=$res.nextEndTime
} while ($res.hasMore)
```

Do not hardcode the API key in commands or files. Set `$env:RENDER_API_KEY` in the shell before running the command.
